properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 12 at 4:55AM PST until January 13 at 4:00AM PST by NWS Spokane WA
properties.description:
...NEXT STORM SYSTEM MOVING IN TODAY...

.Our next weather system is moving in bringing heavy snow to the
mountains and valleys above 1500 ft. Breezy conditions, especially
on exposed ridges, will create areas of blowing snow which could
significantly reduce visibility. Plan on slippery road conditions
which will make travel difficult.

* WHAT...Snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 1 to 3 inches
in the valleys with 4 to 8 inches in the mountains and eastern
Ferry county.

* WHERE...Republic, Inchelium, Wauconda, Chesaw Road, Highway 20
Wauconda Summit, Boulder Creek Road, Sherman Pass, Omak,
Okanogan, Brewster, Oroville, Nespelem, and Disautel Pass.

* WHEN...From 7 AM Sunday to 4 AM PST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. Snow will end in the
evening, but breezy northerly winds overnight will create areas
of blowing and drifting snow which could significantly reduce
visibility.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 4 AM PST MONDAY
